WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.860 --> 00:00:05.280
So Robin's in that building behind you, right?

3
00:00:06.650 --> 00:00:08.400
Get outta my way, bull!

4
00:00:08.400 --> 00:00:17.540
It seems you are all incredibly unaware
that you're committing a major world-class crime.

5
00:00:25.690 --> 00:00:28.350
Get moving right now, get moving right now

6
00:00:28.570 --> 00:00:31.440
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

7
00:00:37.750 --> 00:00:40.480
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

8
00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:43.040
you know what we're searching for

9
00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:46.790
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

10
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.920
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

11
00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:52.940
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

12
00:00:52.940 --> 00:00:54.690
Nothing left to do but press on

13
00:00:54.690 --> 00:01:00.570
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

14
00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:04.370
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

15
00:01:04.370 --> 00:01:07.370
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

16
00:01:07.370 --> 00:01:11.520
Try and stop us if you can

17
00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:12.840
We always pull through

18
00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:16.570
Get moving right now, get moving right now

19
00:01:16.700 --> 00:01:19.530
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

20
00:01:19.580 --> 00:01:22.120
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

21
00:01:22.210 --> 00:01:25.560
and want to hide them from prying eyes

22
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.500
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

23
00:01:28.670 --> 00:01:31.500
Run the direction the compass points in

24
00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:34.210
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

25
00:01:34.210 --> 00:01:36.380
So don't sit back, let's chase it

26
00:01:43.810 --> 00:01:46.470
Get moving right now, get moving right now

27
00:01:46.780 --> 00:01:49.520
We have to pull through ahead of them all

28
00:01:49.610 --> 00:01:52.100
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

29
00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:55.520
I know the future's within our grasp

30
00:01:55.580 --> 00:01:58.610
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

31
00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:01.490
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

32
00:02:01.540 --> 00:02:03.910
All the sadness and the joy we see,

33
00:02:04.130 --> 00:02:06.410
let's etch it in our hearts

34
00:02:15.370 --> 00:02:18.080
Take them all down right here!

35
00:02:18.450 --> 00:02:21.790
Fire! Send the Marines packing!

36
00:02:21.830 --> 00:02:26.210
<b>Signal the Counterstrike</b>

37
00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:31.590
You damn bastards!

38
00:02:42.350 --> 00:02:44.020
I see!

39
00:02:44.020 --> 00:02:48.520
So, back when the brothers were
at death's door in a sea king's stomach,

40
00:02:48.520 --> 00:02:54.070
the Franky Family saved
Sodom and Gomorrah and told them,

41
00:02:54.070 --> 00:02:57.450
"We're full, so we're not gonna eat you."

42
00:02:57.450 --> 00:03:02.160
Since then, they've been
loyal to their savior Franky.

43
00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:05.750
Let me guess.

44
00:03:05.750 --> 00:03:11.880
The Franky Family was eating the sea king
who had swallowed these two, right?

45
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:14.510
Probably.

46
00:03:14.510 --> 00:03:16.010
Well, whatever...

47
00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:19.220
Can you watch where you're going?
You're making me nervous.

48
00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:25.440
He says, "I'll follow Big Bro Franky
for the rest of my life!"

49
00:03:25.440 --> 00:03:29.650
He looks overjoyed to finally meet someone
who understands what he says.

50
00:03:38.070 --> 00:03:43.580
He asked, "By the way, is it okay
that the masked guy didn't hop on with you?"

51
00:03:43.580 --> 00:03:44.540
What?!

52
00:03:48.370 --> 00:03:49.540
What?!

53
00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:52.670
S-Sogeking isn't on board!

54
00:03:54.510 --> 00:03:56.760
Why?! Why?!

55
00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:59.010
Did he fall off?

56
00:03:59.140 --> 00:04:02.010
No... Come to think of it,
he never got on from the start!

57
00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:04.520
Don't tell me he ran away.

58
00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:09.400
<b>Courthouse</b>
<b>Island Gate</b>

59
00:04:09.440 --> 00:04:11.770
<b>Galley-La vs. the Courthouse Guard Force</b>

60
00:04:11.770 --> 00:04:13.190
You bastard!

61
00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:16.280
Stop blocking the path!

62
00:04:16.860 --> 00:04:19.950
If you wish to continue, defeat me first!

63
00:04:19.950 --> 00:04:20.910
Get out...

64
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:23.080
of our way!

65
00:04:26.830 --> 00:04:29.080
It's not gonna be that easy!

66
00:04:30.210 --> 00:04:32.460
Battleship Cannon!

67
00:04:36.420 --> 00:04:40.090
Dammit! There's only
three of them! Do something!

68
00:04:43.350 --> 00:04:46.930
You seem like a strong fighter.

69
00:04:47.430 --> 00:04:50.020
Can you beat them?

70
00:04:50.020 --> 00:04:51.190
Yes, I can!

71
00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:59.200
People waver when faced with uncertainty.

72
00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:06.120
Once they know she needs help,
they won't stop until she's safe!

73
00:05:07.750 --> 00:05:10.370
If anyone can do it... it's that guy!

74
00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:14.540
Take out the one with the rope!

75
00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:16.800
Not gonna happen!

76
00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:21.010
Shrouds and Ratline Knot!

77
00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:23.010
Oh, crap!

78
00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:25.970
End of the line.

79
00:05:25.970 --> 00:05:27.770
Give up.

80
00:05:35.110 --> 00:05:37.320
What's your point?

81
00:05:39.280 --> 00:05:44.240
The World Government is
an expansive and powerful organization

82
00:05:44.240 --> 00:05:48.450
comprised of over 170 nations
across the globe.

83
00:05:48.450 --> 00:05:51.080
Assaulting this government-owned island

84
00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:55.210
amounts to an act of rebellion
against every one of these countries!

85
00:05:55.840 --> 00:06:01.470
To preserve its dignity, the government
will submit each of you to public ridicule

86
00:06:01.470 --> 00:06:04.220
and grant you all a grisly death.

87
00:06:04.220 --> 00:06:06.510
You brought with you a mere few dozen.

88
00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:10.180
You are woefully outnumbered.

89
00:06:10.180 --> 00:06:14.190
All I said... was to get outta my way!

90
00:06:14.190 --> 00:06:16.400
My "point" is that you all have no future.

91
00:06:16.400 --> 00:06:22.320
Even if I were to move, you have
already entered the gates of Enies Lobby.

92
00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:24.450
Fighting is pointless.

93
00:06:24.450 --> 00:06:29.790
You have seen our Six Powers firsthand
at Galley-La's mansion,

94
00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:33.790
and you know your fighting prowess
pales in comparison.

95
00:06:36.630 --> 00:06:38.380
Yeah, that's true,

96
00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:40.500
but for some reason,

97
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:43.590
losing just doesn't feel possible right now!

98
00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:48.550
Gum-Gum...

99
00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:50.260
Iron Body.

100
00:06:50.810 --> 00:06:52.220
...Rifle!

101
00:07:04.150 --> 00:07:05.910
What...?

102
00:07:05.910 --> 00:07:10.990
I don't remember him being this powerful
when I fought him at the mansion!

103
00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:14.160
Gatling!

104
00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:15.160
Shave!

105
00:07:43.730 --> 00:07:47.200
World this... Government that...

106
00:07:47.200 --> 00:07:49.450
Do whatever you want with that.

107
00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:58.370
We just came here... to take Robin back!

108
00:08:08.050 --> 00:08:09.640
Wh-Wh-What're we gonna do?!

109
00:08:12.350 --> 00:08:13.560
At this point...

110
00:08:14.060 --> 00:08:17.270
going back and getting him
is no longer an option.

111
00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:21.230
I'm sure he'll work things out on his own.

112
00:08:21.230 --> 00:08:23.900
But the island's swarming with guards!

113
00:08:24.280 --> 00:08:27.070
He isn't Luffy. If he's
by himself, his life will be–

114
00:08:27.070 --> 00:08:33.280
Even if we don't realize it, every one of us
grows stronger with each challenge we face.

115
00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:37.040
That guy has faced life-or-death situations
on every island we've been to.

116
00:08:37.040 --> 00:08:41.630
No one on our crew would die so easily.

117
00:08:47.130 --> 00:08:49.720
Look! We're almost to the courthouse!

118
00:08:51.890 --> 00:08:53.470
Bring them down at all costs!

119
00:09:00.560 --> 00:09:02.480
Oh, crap! The king bull!

120
00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:05.360
All right! We took one of 'em down!

121
00:09:06.190 --> 00:09:07.900
Sodom!

122
00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:14.410
Sodom! This is bad!
He needs immediate treatment!

123
00:09:14.740 --> 00:09:18.120
Sodom! Stand tall! Don't fall yet!

124
00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:21.790
You guys gotta jump over right now!

125
00:09:21.790 --> 00:09:25.750
Get the lead out! Sodom is finished!

126
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:30.050
That shell hit 'im square in the chest!

127
00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:31.630
Hurry, before he falls!

128
00:09:32.010 --> 00:09:35.350
No one's getting saved
unless you guys keep moving!

129
00:09:47.440 --> 00:09:49.400
He said, "Go!"

130
00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:05.130
It's coming down!

131
00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:27.520
No one's on board!

132
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:29.070
What?!

133
00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:31.440
Come on...

134
00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:34.910
Let's go, Gomorrah!

135
00:10:37.240 --> 00:10:38.830
<b>Island Gate</b>

136
00:10:43.830 --> 00:10:46.580
I wasn't able to get on the king bull.

137
00:10:46.580 --> 00:10:49.460
What do I do? I'm way behind now.

138
00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:54.090
But wow, those shipwrights are amazing!

139
00:10:54.800 --> 00:10:57.720
Anyway, I'm already off the crew.

140
00:10:57.720 --> 00:11:00.390
Should I just run?

141
00:11:06.810 --> 00:11:09.480
N-N-No! Running is the last thing I'll do!

142
00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:14.320
I'm Usopp! I'm a man! I went so far
as to hide my identity to follow them!

143
00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:18.200
Robin's risking her life to protect us,
and the situation's dire!

144
00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:20.450
I will persevere to the end!

145
00:11:20.950 --> 00:11:22.200
All right...!

146
00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:24.580
There's only one way to catch up to everyone!

147
00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:32.340
Operation: Disguise Myself as a Government Agent
and Pass by Them Unnoticed!

148
00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:35.630
Yes, very good.

149
00:11:36.510 --> 00:11:37.640
I'll...

150
00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:38.970
Huh?!

151
00:11:41.140 --> 00:11:43.270
What?! What?! Some kind
of watery ambush?!

152
00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:45.770
Enemy attack! Enemy attack!

153
00:11:45.770 --> 00:11:48.270
Oh, the shame!

154
00:11:50.900 --> 00:11:53.900
The giant woke up!

155
00:11:53.900 --> 00:11:56.650
We screwed up in our fiftieth year!

156
00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:59.910
Oimo's sorry, Chiefs!

157
00:11:58.530 --> 00:11:59.910
Chiefs?

158
00:12:01.530 --> 00:12:04.540
We are a disgrace to Elbaph!

159
00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:06.960
E-Elbaph?

160
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:11.040
Elbaph... Chiefs...

161
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:12.670
Just a moment!

162
00:12:12.670 --> 00:12:16.220
I-Is it possible that you're from Elbaph,
the island of warriors?!

163
00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:18.970
Who are you?!

164
00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:22.140
I-I-I am Sogeking from Sniper Island.

165
00:12:22.140 --> 00:12:25.930
C-Can you elaborate on what you just said?

166
00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:28.480
Please...

167
00:12:28.480 --> 00:12:32.480
It's pointless to tell you about it, but...

168
00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:39.820
Oimo and Kashi were pirates
up until 100 years ago.

169
00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:42.700
We ran wild all over the world.

170
00:12:42.700 --> 00:12:45.870
But one day on a certain island...

171
00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:49.330
Our two chiefs began to battle one another.

172
00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:55.710
The crew split apart, and everyone
ended up returning to their homeland.

173
00:12:55.710 --> 00:12:58.220
It was a life-or-death battle between warriors.

174
00:12:58.220 --> 00:13:01.550
We expected the winner
to at least come back to the island;

175
00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:05.720
however, several decades passed,
and neither one returned.

176
00:13:05.720 --> 00:13:10.730
It was fifty years later when Oimo and Kashi
thought something might've gone wrong,

177
00:13:10.730 --> 00:13:13.400
so we set out to sea to bring them home.

178
00:13:13.810 --> 00:13:17.820
But we got caught by the Marines,
and they made us tell them everything.

179
00:13:17.820 --> 00:13:21.860
In return, they told us a shocking story.

180
00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:28.620
They said that our two mighty chiefs were
being held in the government's huge prison!

181
00:13:28.620 --> 00:13:29.710
Huh?!

182
00:13:29.710 --> 00:13:32.960
That was about fifty years ago.

183
00:13:34.040 --> 00:13:36.750
The government gave us these conditions:

184
00:13:36.750 --> 00:13:40.880
If Oimo and Kashi served
the government for 100 years—

185
00:13:40.880 --> 00:13:45.550
that is, if we could protect this gate
on Enies Lobby for an entire century—

186
00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:51.190
they'd release the chiefs
and let us all go home to Elbaph.

187
00:13:51.190 --> 00:13:55.650
Since giants live for 300 years,
we figured 100 years wouldn't be so bad.

188
00:13:55.650 --> 00:13:59.110
So we accepted and kept fighting
these past fifty years.

189
00:13:59.110 --> 00:14:03.280
But today, pirates came
and broke open the gate!

190
00:14:03.280 --> 00:14:05.660
I never imagined this would happen!

191
00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.030
Dammit!

192
00:14:07.030 --> 00:14:10.910
The chiefs will be kept in prison
till their dying breaths!

193
00:14:12.040 --> 00:14:13.620
Hey, hey! H-H-Hold on a sec!

194
00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:15.670
That's funny–

195
00:14:15.670 --> 00:14:17.420
What's "funny" about it?!

196
00:14:17.420 --> 00:14:20.170
If you're gonna laugh at our pride, then–

197
00:14:20.170 --> 00:14:23.590
No, no! I don't mean funny-ha-ha,
I meant funny-weird!

198
00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:25.470
Now you think it's "weird"?!

199
00:14:25.470 --> 00:14:30.640
Listen! During our journey here,
we actually met those two!

200
00:14:34.190 --> 00:14:37.940
The two you've been talking about—
the warriors of Elbaph, Dorry and Brogy—

201
00:14:37.940 --> 00:14:43.070
have been fighting an evenly matched duel
on that island for the past 100 years!

202
00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:50.160
Wha...?! How... do you know their names?!

203
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:52.000
No, that's impossible!

204
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:55.790
You want more proof? Well, I've got it!

205
00:15:01.710 --> 00:15:03.090
Like so...

206
00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:18.730
Don't believe me?!
What else do you wanna know?!

207
00:15:23.650 --> 00:15:25.200
About their weapons?!

208
00:15:29.490 --> 00:15:30.620
Their techniques?!

209
00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:34.080
That's 73,466 duels...

210
00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:35.750
I know everything!

211
00:15:35.750 --> 00:15:39.460
...and 73,466 draws.

212
00:15:39.460 --> 00:15:45.130
We really met them!

213
00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:54.980
They got caught fifty years ago?!
You were told a whopper of a lie!

214
00:15:58.390 --> 00:16:05.610
<b>Courthouse</b>
<b>Rocketman</b>

215
00:16:17.410 --> 00:16:20.040
It's coming! Take aim!

216
00:16:21.290 --> 00:16:23.630
Let it get closer!

217
00:16:23.630 --> 00:16:26.470
That's artillery fire! Dodge it, Gomorrah!

218
00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:33.890
This central path is no good!
They're all set up to ambush us!

219
00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:35.220
We've gotta take a detour!

220
00:16:42.980 --> 00:16:44.690
You won't get away!

221
00:16:48.200 --> 00:16:49.740
Sodom...

222
00:16:49.740 --> 00:16:51.410
Stop!

223
00:17:05.130 --> 00:17:06.590
Chopper...

224
00:17:08.130 --> 00:17:10.050
Huh? The baby transponder snail?!

225
00:17:10.760 --> 00:17:12.260
Hello? Who is it?

226
00:17:13.470 --> 00:17:14.680
It's us.

227
00:17:14.680 --> 00:17:15.850
Old lady Kokoro!

228
00:17:15.850 --> 00:17:17.100
Why're you calling...?

229
00:17:18.600 --> 00:17:20.600
Sounds like you guys are still alive.

230
00:17:20.600 --> 00:17:22.810
Good, 'cause I forgot to tell you something.

231
00:17:22.810 --> 00:17:26.730
I know you're all busy,
so I'll be quick. Listen up.

232
00:17:27.440 --> 00:17:32.240
On Paulie's map, you won't see a path
from the courthouse to the Tower of Justice.

233
00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:35.530
She's right. I wondered about that.

234
00:17:35.530 --> 00:17:39.540
Look at the courthouse.
There's a tower on either side, right?

235
00:17:39.540 --> 00:17:40.660
Yeah, there is.

236
00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:45.670
There's a lever on the top floor of each tower.

237
00:17:45.670 --> 00:17:50.920
When you pull both, a drawbridge lowers
from the courthouse to the Tower of Justice.

238
00:17:50.920 --> 00:17:53.930
How in the heck do you know all that?

239
00:17:54.260 --> 00:17:57.470
I came here with Tom
to fix the bridge a long time ago.

240
00:17:57.470 --> 00:17:59.890
That ungrateful, idiot-run government!

241
00:17:59.890 --> 00:18:01.890
Don't take it out on me.

242
00:18:01.890 --> 00:18:03.600
Chimney wants to talk to you too.

243
00:18:03.980 --> 00:18:07.110
Hello, pirate lady! Can you hear me?

244
00:18:07.110 --> 00:18:09.070
Whoa! What is it, Chimney?

245
00:18:09.070 --> 00:18:15.160
So, I saw the rubber pirate guy
on the rooftop of the courthouse.

246
00:18:16.830 --> 00:18:18.370
Really?! Luffy was there?

247
00:18:18.700 --> 00:18:23.830
I saw rubble collapsing there, too,
so it looks like he's really letting loose.

248
00:18:24.250 --> 00:18:25.580
On the rooftop?

249
00:18:25.580 --> 00:18:27.000
Got it. Thanks!

250
00:18:27.340 --> 00:18:33.260
Pirate girl, keep the transponder snail
connected so that I can stay in the know.

251
00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:34.090
Roger!

252
00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:35.140
So...

253
00:18:36.180 --> 00:18:38.510
So now we know where to go.

254
00:18:38.510 --> 00:18:40.430
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

255
00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:47.230
Alright, you guys go straight
to the courthouse and meet up with Straw Hat.

256
00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:48.980
Okay.

257
00:18:53.240 --> 00:18:56.620
We're gonna split into two groups
and bring down that drawbridge.

258
00:18:58.080 --> 00:19:00.990
Take us to the courthouse, Gomorrah!

259
00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:11.510
Gomorrah!

260
00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:21.850
Dammit! Who are they?!

261
00:19:27.650 --> 00:19:37.780
Tattoo: "Guilty"

262
00:19:34.030 --> 00:19:37.780
It won't be that easy... you damn trash.

263
00:19:41.910 --> 00:19:45.410
All right! The second one is down too!

264
00:19:47.040 --> 00:19:49.420
We've stopped the pirates dead in their tracks!

265
00:19:49.420 --> 00:19:51.170
Surround them and take them out!

266
00:19:51.170 --> 00:19:53.880
Calling all Enies Lobby troops!

267
00:19:53.880 --> 00:19:59.510
At the center of Block D in the southeast,
we brought down the king bull the pirates were riding!

268
00:19:59.510 --> 00:20:03.890
This is a call to all troops
to regroup and seal off Block D!

269
00:20:04.350 --> 00:20:05.270
I repeat!

270
00:20:05.270 --> 00:20:08.520
All troops, regroup and seal off Block D!

271
00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:11.770
Looks like the jury delivered the verdict.

272
00:20:12.570 --> 00:20:15.030
No one can beat them.

273
00:20:17.490 --> 00:20:18.740
– Just say something!
– Just say something!

274
00:20:18.740 --> 00:20:19.700
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

275
00:20:19.700 --> 00:20:21.320
We'll capture them right away!

276
00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:26.280
<b>Courthouse</b>

277
00:20:26.790 --> 00:20:30.170
The guards that we passed
are catching up. This isn't good.

278
00:20:30.790 --> 00:20:33.380
They're piling in from
the front and the sides too.

279
00:20:33.880 --> 00:20:35.840
And the artillery's aimed right at us!

280
00:20:37.010 --> 00:20:39.840
This is terrible! There are thousands of them!

281
00:20:40.340 --> 00:20:45.060
If we get surrounded by them
in a place like this, we'll be goners!

282
00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:49.440
<b>The Tower of Justice</b>

283
00:20:48.690 --> 00:20:51.440
You're one lucky lady.

284
00:20:51.440 --> 00:20:53.770
Most people don't get
a rescue squad, y'know.

285
00:20:54.230 --> 00:21:00.110
Well, it's not like I'm jealous
that my underlings aren't here to rescue me!

286
00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:20.880
Oh, wait, you guys.

287
00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:22.640
I almost forgot.

288
00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:24.100
Take these with you.

289
00:21:29.020 --> 00:21:31.600
Wait! Aren't those devil fruits?!

290
00:21:36.190 --> 00:21:38.570
Could it be...

291
00:21:38.570 --> 00:21:43.280
truly true?!

292
00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:46.330
I've never seen one before!

293
00:21:46.330 --> 00:21:49.580
The same goes for me!

294
00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:51.960
Not good! Keep those away from me!

295
00:21:52.540 --> 00:21:55.380
What's all this hullabaloo, Jabra?

296
00:21:55.380 --> 00:21:57.500
You idiot! Don't you know?

297
00:21:57.500 --> 00:22:03.090
Those with devil fruit powers have
an actual devil dwelling inside their bodies!

298
00:22:03.090 --> 00:22:05.800
That means, if I get close to that fruit,

299
00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:13.350
its devil will jump out and start fighting
the devil in me, causing my body to explode!

300
00:22:13.940 --> 00:22:15.230
You pulling my leg?

301
00:22:16.690 --> 00:22:18.820
How foolish.

302
00:22:18.820 --> 00:22:23.360
Only a sloppy intelligence agent
would be misled by a rumor.

303
00:22:23.360 --> 00:22:29.830
Grand Line scientists have already discovered
how the fruits transfer their powers.

304
00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:34.540
You are talking about an instance
when a person ingests two fruits.

305
00:22:34.540 --> 00:22:37.710
The individual disintegrates
until nothing remains.

306
00:22:37.710 --> 00:22:40.800
Greedy idiots cause their own downfall.

307
00:22:40.800 --> 00:22:43.430
There's an inherent risk with just one fruit;

308
00:22:43.430 --> 00:22:48.560
they should've realized how the curse
might amplify upon eating a second.

309
00:22:49.680 --> 00:22:51.850
What?! Is that so?!

310
00:22:51.850 --> 00:22:56.520
But Chief, it's crazy to think you managed
to get your hands on two devil fruits.

311
00:22:57.060 --> 00:22:58.230
Where'd you get them?

312
00:22:58.230 --> 00:23:01.230
I have all sorts of connections.

313
00:23:01.230 --> 00:23:03.320
Eat them to prepare for the future.

314
00:23:04.780 --> 00:23:07.450
Become even stronger, CP9!

315
00:23:07.450 --> 00:23:09.950
But I'll give you fair warning.

316
00:23:09.950 --> 00:23:13.960
I don't know what kinds of devils
dwell in those fruits.

317
00:23:13.960 --> 00:23:17.040
It's hard to believe these fruits
are of this world.

318
00:23:17.040 --> 00:23:20.670
They give off what feels like a gravitational pull.

319
00:23:20.670 --> 00:23:22.800
Neither is listed in the reference books.

320
00:23:23.130 --> 00:23:25.380
That seems to be how they normally are.

321
00:23:25.380 --> 00:23:29.800
It's said you can infer the fruit's name
from the powers you exhibit,

322
00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:32.810
but it's a crapshoot
as to what powers you gain.

323
00:23:33.180 --> 00:23:37.600
Your life takes a turn for the worse if you
obtain an offbeat power with this gamble.

324
00:23:37.600 --> 00:23:40.610
Add losing the ability to swim to that...

325
00:23:41.520 --> 00:23:45.110
No matter the power,
what counts is how it's used.

326
00:23:45.110 --> 00:23:47.780
In all likelihood, you won't become weaker.

327
00:23:47.780 --> 00:23:50.910
Being unable to swim is
no big drawback, either.

328
00:23:50.910 --> 00:23:57.790
Countless sailors find death in their
quest for just one devil fruit.

329
00:23:58.500 --> 00:24:01.460
Go ahead and eat them. Let's have some fun.

330
00:24:02.340 --> 00:24:05.970
Kalifa, don't do it!
Nothing good will come of this.

331
00:24:05.970 --> 00:24:08.340
It tastes like turds. Literal turds!

332
00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:12.060
Jabra doesn't want
Kaku and Kalifa to get stronger.

333
00:24:13.100 --> 00:24:14.600
Such is the truth!

334
00:24:14.600 --> 00:24:20.650
Jealously and envy tarnish a man's good name.

335
00:24:23.980 --> 00:24:26.400
Shut up, you jerks!

336
00:24:26.400 --> 00:24:28.740
Hey, you two! Think about it carefully!

337
00:24:28.740 --> 00:24:31.780
The right buyer will
net you hundreds of millions,

338
00:24:31.780 --> 00:24:34.700
but one bite will curse you for life!

339
00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:45.920
Well, you've piqued my interest.

340
00:24:46.840 --> 00:24:49.090
If this fruit's a winner, I'll welcome it.

341
00:24:51.340 --> 00:24:53.640
They ate them, damn it!

342
00:25:02.190 --> 00:25:03.190
What's the matter?!

343
00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:10.410
Have you noticed any physical changes?!

344
00:25:20.920 --> 00:25:21.830
– It's disgusting.
– It's disgusting.

345
00:25:21.830 --> 00:25:23.330
Say that sooner!

346
00:25:23.330 --> 00:25:24.590
It tastes awful!

347
00:25:24.590 --> 00:25:26.210
You already said that!

348
00:25:26.210 --> 00:25:29.920
You should say that before
consuming the whole thing!

349
00:25:31.260 --> 00:25:35.180
Hey, try doing something!
What kind of powers did you get?!

350
00:25:36.850 --> 00:25:39.600
I don't feel like anything is different.

351
00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:42.980
You'll soon notice the enormity of the change.

352
00:25:44.480 --> 00:25:46.900
You've been reborn with new abilities.

353
00:25:46.900 --> 00:25:48.490
I look forward to seeing them.

354
00:25:48.490 --> 00:25:52.860
At the very least, get a handle
on your abilities during this downtime.

355
00:25:52.910 --> 00:25:57.330
Depending on the chief's orders,
they might get an early field test.

356
00:25:57.950 --> 00:26:03.460
although Blueno did get impatient
and joined the festivities before us.

357
00:26:04.160 --> 00:26:08.630
<b>Courthouse</b>
<b>Rocketman</b>

358
00:26:04.210 --> 00:26:08.630
<b>Near the Island Gate</b>

359
00:26:13.890 --> 00:26:15.010
Hey, look!

360
00:26:19.890 --> 00:26:21.100
All right!

361
00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:23.850
Oimo and Kashi are back in action!

362
00:26:23.850 --> 00:26:25.360
Of all the rotten...

363
00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:29.940
We don't have the energy
for another fight with them...

364
00:26:33.030 --> 00:26:34.280
Is this it for us?!

365
00:26:37.700 --> 00:26:40.120
Hurry over here and stomp them to pieces!

366
00:26:40.120 --> 00:26:42.960
Take these three out, you giants!

367
00:26:50.920 --> 00:26:53.630
How...

368
00:26:53.630 --> 00:26:56.050
...dare you...

369
00:26:59.510 --> 00:27:00.970
– Huh?
– Huh?

370
00:27:00.970 --> 00:27:02.980
– ...deceive us?!
– ...deceive us?!

371
00:27:09.070 --> 00:27:12.400
Wh-What the hell?! Those two
went over to the enemy's side!

372
00:27:13.070 --> 00:27:15.820
Before we rejoice
over the safety of our chiefs...

373
00:27:15.820 --> 00:27:18.320
before we grieve over our wasted years...

374
00:27:18.320 --> 00:27:22.080
We'll let loose our rage
upon these deceitful cowards!

375
00:27:22.830 --> 00:27:26.210
Let's go together... King of Snipers!

376
00:27:33.840 --> 00:27:35.260
I strongly concur!

377
00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:37.840
The time has come to signal the counterstrike!

378
00:27:37.840 --> 00:27:40.390
Hurry, to our brothers-in-arms!

379
00:27:40.430 --> 00:27:45.180
<b>Courthouse</b>

380
00:27:40.430 --> 00:27:45.140
<b>Luffy vs. Blueno
Courthouse Rooftop</b>

381
00:27:53.070 --> 00:27:54.690
I underestimated you.

382
00:27:56.070 --> 00:27:57.160
Well, don't!

383
00:27:57.160 --> 00:28:00.700
I never thought he would
keep pace with shave.

384
00:28:00.700 --> 00:28:02.200
I should be careful.

385
00:28:03.040 --> 00:28:05.620
Hitting a rubber man will be ineffective, right?

386
00:28:05.620 --> 00:28:06.870
Moon Walk!

387
00:28:09.460 --> 00:28:10.960
Gum-Gum...

388
00:28:10.960 --> 00:28:11.920
Tempest Kick!

389
00:28:17.970 --> 00:28:19.140
Iron Body!

390
00:28:21.180 --> 00:28:22.180
Wheel!

391
00:28:32.570 --> 00:28:33.900
Door Door!

392
00:28:38.280 --> 00:28:40.530
Huh? A-A door opened on the ground!

393
00:28:40.530 --> 00:28:41.660
Door Door.

394
00:28:44.910 --> 00:28:46.450
Wh-What the heck?!

395
00:28:46.450 --> 00:28:49.000
Were these small doors here before?!

396
00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:54.300
C-C-Crap! I got stuck! Dammit! These things...

397
00:28:54.300 --> 00:28:57.880
You! What's this?! What'd you do?!
Is this a devil fruit power?!

398
00:28:57.880 --> 00:29:00.390
I'm a door human
with Door-Door devil fruit powers.

399
00:29:00.760 --> 00:29:04.100
I can turn anything into a door!

400
00:29:07.560 --> 00:29:09.060
Revolving Door.

401
00:29:11.980 --> 00:29:14.230
What?! What?! Wh-What's going on?!

402
00:29:14.230 --> 00:29:15.730
Everything's spinning!

403
00:29:16.990 --> 00:29:20.200
Wh-Wh-Which way is forward?! Make it stop!

404
00:29:20.200 --> 00:29:21.320
Tempest Kick!

405
00:29:31.790 --> 00:29:33.080
Hey, cook!

406
00:29:33.080 --> 00:29:34.790
Yeah, I saw it.

407
00:29:34.790 --> 00:29:37.960
Luffy's already fighting CP9.

408
00:29:37.960 --> 00:29:38.920
– What?!
– What?!

409
00:29:38.920 --> 00:29:40.590
I-Is that true?!

410
00:29:40.590 --> 00:29:42.300
Dammit! We got off to a late start!

411
00:29:42.930 --> 00:29:46.930
But how do we break out
of this encirclement?!

412
00:29:46.930 --> 00:29:50.310
Gomorrah took all these flail hits,
and now he can't move!

413
00:29:50.310 --> 00:29:54.560
Fire! Shoot those pirates off that beast!

414
00:29:58.320 --> 00:30:00.280
There's only one way out!

415
00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:03.200
Yeah, we're gonna make
a dash for the courthouse!

416
00:30:03.910 --> 00:30:05.490
Looks like we'll have to.

417
00:30:07.200 --> 00:30:09.660
All right, let's go, boys!

418
00:30:09.660 --> 00:30:10.750
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

419
00:30:10.750 --> 00:30:11.960
Wait!

420
00:30:12.370 --> 00:30:14.880
Nobody get off!

421
00:30:15.590 --> 00:30:16.500
Chopper?!

422
00:30:21.010 --> 00:30:23.510
Hold on tight!

423
00:30:39.280 --> 00:30:40.860
Gomorrah...

424
00:30:40.860 --> 00:30:43.490
Gomorrah says so!

425
00:30:43.860 --> 00:30:45.200
Th-The monster...

426
00:30:45.200 --> 00:30:46.660
...is still alive!

427
00:30:46.660 --> 00:30:49.370
Fire! Use your rockets to take it down!

428
00:30:49.370 --> 00:30:51.120
Shoot the monster!

429
00:30:51.120 --> 00:30:53.710
Fight back! Protect Gomorrah!

430
00:31:01.510 --> 00:31:04.840
Go! Gomorrah!

431
00:31:09.520 --> 00:31:16.060
I know there’s something that I need to say,

432
00:31:16.440 --> 00:31:20.030
but I can’t seem to find the words

433
00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:27.910
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

434
00:31:27.910 --> 00:31:33.670
And now there’s something right in front of me,

435
00:31:34.870 --> 00:31:38.380
a light that shines brighter than gold

436
00:31:38.750 --> 00:31:43.760
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

437
00:31:43.760 --> 00:31:50.350
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

438
00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:56.600
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

439
00:31:56.810 --> 00:31:59.610
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

440
00:31:59.900 --> 00:32:02.690
Yeah, we just take it day by day

441
00:32:02.990 --> 00:32:09.240
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

442
00:32:09.530 --> 00:32:15.870
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
